article.linkText: Last 1 standing: Texas knocks out Spartans
article.story: EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Chris Hill scored 18 points and Alan Anderson had 15 points and nine rebounds in No. 3 Michigan State's 85-81 exhibition victory over Team Nike on Thursday night. Paul Davis added 14 points for the Spartans, and Kelvin Torbert had 10 points, despite playing just one minute in the second half before twisting an ankle. Former Wisconsin player Charlie Wills led Team Nike with 20 points. Kenny Williams added 18 points.
